#eNCA Courtesy #DStv403 EAST LONDON - Officials from the Buffalo City Metro are conducting oversight visits at various taverns in Scenery Park. The goal is to check who is flouting by-laws and if tavern owners possess the necessary liquor trading licenses. READ: Tavern Tragedy | Institute calls for stricter alcohol regulations The crackdown comes over a week after 21 teenagers tragically died at  Enyobeni tavern in East London. The tavern is infamous for allegedly allowing teenagers into the establishment. WATCH | Inside Enyobeni Tavern where 21 teens died The visit to the area's taverns is in conjunction with the Eastern Cape Liquor Board and Safety authorities. This visit is aimed at raising awareness, doing safety inspections and monitoring compliance.